This is a collection of resources common to many projects.

There are OpenShift image streams, templates and pipelines.

Many applications are located in registry.redhat.io, so you need a valid secret in place. Please see https://access.redhat.com/RegistryAuthentication#registry-service-accounts-for-shared-environments-4

----

oc apply -f <registry-credentials>.yaml

oc secrets link default <registry-credentials>

----

Provision PostgreSQL

oc process -p POSTGRESQL_DATABASE="c3Nv" -p POSTGRESQL_USER="c3Nv" -p POSTGRESQL_PASSWORD="c3Nv" -f template-postgresql.yaml | oc apply -f -

----

Provision AMQ Broker

oc process -p MQ_QUEUES="orderCommand" -p MQ_TOPICS="" -f template-amqbroker.yaml | oc apply -f -

----

Provision Red Hat Single Sign-On

# change variables in deploysso.sh
./deploysso.sh
